    {
      "id": 33349,
      "name": "AlexGS",
      "username": "AlexGS",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/e495f1/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2023-09-26T16:00:10.804Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hi All,</p>\n<p>Thank you for the feedback and the discussion.</p>\n<p>I would need to correct myself a bit: I can\u2019t prove if any other apps do release the BT connection when they are put in background or not. What I\u2019m 100% sure though is that it\u2019s only the Trainer Day app that still sends the mode and power targets to the trainer after the workout is done and even if the app is in the background.</p>\n<p>I would say if the app would still keep the connection open but would stop (perhaps it can be configurable) sending the mode and power targets after the workout completion it would work for me perfectly!</p>\n<p>I was too wondering why nobody mentioned this before and I\u2019m pretty sure I was just lucky figuring it out because of me loving to do a free ride in Zwift post workout. It greatly helps with recovery and I\u2019m doing it constantly. Wouldn\u2019t I have this routine it would take me \u201cyears\u201d to narrow it down. Plus with TrainerPeeks integration it\u2019s so tempting to send all workouts to Zwift (though that makes Pretzelfesting harder)\u2026</p>\n<p>Alex.</p>",
