      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/e495f1/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2023-10-31T17:52:50.576Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I have Android. Should I try running the app/workout on an Android? I think even the lower recovery intervals had that issue it\u2019s just the scale get to 1w or lower for those. I can also try some 120% Vo2Max intervals to see how it behaves. <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"></p>\n<p>Btw, I have a friend who also uses Kickr bike and I made him to try the TD app. He used it without Zwift or any other apps and he reports the same drop outs. Though he didn\u2019t save the activity so I can\u2019t share it.</p>",
